{
  "id": 5076692209106944,
  "name": "WebRequest.SecurityInfo in Controlled Frame",
  "summary": "This feature introduces a WebRequest.SecurityInfo API for [ControlledFrame](https://developer.chrome.com/docs/iwa/controlled-frame). It allows a web app to intercept an HTTPS, WSS, or WebTransport request to a server, retrieve the server's certificate fingerprint (as verified by the browser), and then use that fingerprint to manually verify the certificate of a separate raw TCP/UDP connection to the same server. This provides a simple way for the app to confirm it's communicating with the correct server.",
